cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.NA, cs.SI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of the sum rate performance of linear precoding techniques in a broadcast channel with limited feedback. This falls under the purview of information theory. 
2. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper discusses the optimization of power allocation and feedback in multi-user systems. This is a characteristic of multi-agent systems. 
3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper derives deterministic approximations of the empirical signal-to-interference plus noise ratio (SINR) at the receivers, which can be used to solve various practical optimization problems. This involves numerical analysis techniques. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the optimization of power allocation and feedback in a network of users. This can be considered as a social and information network problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not directly related to multimedia, the paper deals with the optimization of power allocation and feedback in a broadcast channel, which can be considered as a multimedia communication problem.
